<br>
Instead, chanelling is sort of a double-whammy against casters.  First we have no armor and no hitpoints, thus are in a life-threatening situation when we end up tanking in the first place.  Then, coupled to that already massive risk, we have the fact that our spells are quite likely not going to go off.<br>
<br>
I personally don't understand which way the mitigation to cloth went in the patch, but it should have gone up, not down.  Or at the very least there should be some level based check outside of your chanelling skill.  e.g. 1%/level flat chance your spell will go off.  If that fails, then it checks your chanelling skill.<br>
<br>
It has always seemed odd to me why chanelling was as hard as it is, especially since higher level spells tend to be fairly long on the cast times.<br>
<br>
-- Hika<br>
